entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: do you consider yourself an introvert

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yeah

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what do you do to relax

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i watch tv mostly listen to music like smooth jazz like relaxing music

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what do you do when you are annoyed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i breathe i listen to music i try to do whatever i can to calm down

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are some things that make you really mad

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: the things that really make me mad is like when i am disrespected sort of per se when thing when like when bad things happen that is what really irritates me that is all

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am i am good as far as i think i am but there is times where i feel like i can not but i try as hard as i can to control it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i argued with my fiance about a couple of weeks about some financial issues eh but that was it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever served in the military

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i have not

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i have not

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no i have not

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: fairly easy most of the time but if there are like noises around me then it gets a little harder like a a neighbor partying or or loud noises in the house then it is hard but usually it is easy

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am just like really tired in the morning like i do not have a attitude or anything but i am just like tired in the morning like i need more sleep when i wake up

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i have been feeling okay just i am down sometimes i sleep a little than i am i sleep more than i am used to but i have been okay

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: is there anything you regret

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no no not really i mean i have had some bad experiences but for the most part i do not regret anything

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what advice would you give yourself ten or twenty years ago

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: to just do what to do what i have to do strive really hard take care of my business and that is about it

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: when was the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i felt really happy on christmas when i got engaged

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about something you did recently that you really enjoyed

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i enjoy going to nevada to celebrate my birthday i enjoy spending time with my family and my friends

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how close are you to your family

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: fairly close there were some things that brought us apart but we are trying to get close again
